chunk: Izidor Maklary is a Budapest-based software developer who transitioned from joinery to programming. His journey began in the Alps of Austria, where he learned about workflows, consistency, and task dependencies. He wrote his first code in CNC programming during joinery school, which sparked his interest in software development. Izidor is passionate about the flexibility and versatility of coding, with expertise in TypeScript, Node.js, and Cloudflare Workers. He also enjoys producing music, cycling, and playing table tennis, and has a deep appreciation for arts and contemporary music.

Izidor's portfolio project aims to provide a clean summary of his past activities, integrating an AI chatbot for tailored information. He used Next.js for the frontend and API handling, with content managed via Notion pages and rendered with custom React components. The AI tasks are managed through OpenAI APIs, ensuring scalable and accurate responses. The portfolio showcases not only his learnings but also serves as a demonstration of his technical skills.

Izidor's technical skills include proficiency in TypeScript, Node.js, and Cloudflare Workers. He has experience with Vercel, Next.js, React, and the Notion SDK. He has also worked with AWS, Lambda, DynamoDB, and GraphQL, demonstrating his ability to handle complex backend and serverless setups. His work with Bubbly-Doo involved cutting-edge technologies and open-source contributions, further expanding his technical expertise.

Izidor's journey in web development began with a 7-month bootcamp at Becode Antwerp, focusing on teamwork and self-guided learning. This experience taught him how to grow as a developer, emphasizing the importance of asking questions and formulating them effectively. The bootcamp provided a strong foundation for his career in software development.

At Bubbly-Doo, Izidor worked on various backend projects, including the development of a new GraphQL API and dashboard. He learned about objection (Knex-based ORM), Express.js, and serverless setups with AWS/Lambda. He created a shared logic layer to avoid code duplication and implemented GraphQL subscriptions for real-time updates. His work resulted in a fast and efficient internal dashboard still in use today.

Izidor's first interaction with Next.js was during the development of Bubbly-Doo's internal dashboard. He used Apollo Client for handling backend GraphQL queries and implemented scroll-based pagination for order lists. The dashboard supports batch operations and robust filtering, ensuring efficient order management. It continues to serve many users effectively.

Over nearly four years, Izidor integrated with 11 printing partners worldwide for Bubbly-Doo. He set up Cloudflare Workers for order placement and AWS/Lambda for status post-backs, overcoming challenges to ensure smooth operations. His work in printer integrations highlights his ability to manage complex technical tasks and collaborate with global partners.

Izidor's technical skills are extensive, including TypeScript, Node.js, Cloudflare Workers, Vercel, Next.js, React, AWS, Lambda, DynamoDB, GraphQL, and Apollo Client. His experience with cutting-edge technologies and open-source contributions demonstrates his commitment to continuous learning and innovation in software development.

Izidor's portfolio project leverages a simple stack with exhaustive tooling from Vercel, Next.js for frontend and API, and Notion SDK for content management. The AI chatbot integration uses OpenAI APIs through @ai/sdk, enabling scalable and accurate responses. This project showcases his ability to create maintainable and innovative solutions in web development.

Izidor's work at Bubbly-Doo involved using TypeScript on both frontend and backend, exploring experimental tools, and contributing to the open-source community. His role as an intern included creating a new GraphQL API and dashboard, learning about objection, Express.js, and serverless setups. His contributions led to significant improvements in the company's technical infrastructure.

Izidor's transition from joinery to programming highlights his adaptability and passion for learning. His journey from CNC programming in joinery school to becoming a proficient software developer showcases his dedication to mastering new skills and applying them effectively in his career.
